data.name: pbHelpSqlServerObjects.ToolTip
data.value: This is a list of tables and views to run LayerGen against, separated by a ";". Click the button next to the text box to bring up a graphical table and view selector. Tables must have a primary key defined or else the table will be skipped!

data.name: pictureBox4.ToolTip
data.value: If checked, LayerGen will automatically create methods that allow data to be serialized in various formats, such as JSON and XML. These methods will require a reference to Newtonsoft's Json.Net library, which can be freely downloaded from their website.

data.name: pictureBox6.ToolTip
data.value: If checked, code will be generated that will allow you to retrieve data through a Sql statement or a stored procedure and dynamically bind it to a strongly typed class. This feature will require .NET 4.0 or higher.

data.name: pictureBox9.ToolTip
data.value: Check this box if you want to create custom package names for both the model, dao, service and controller layers. If this box is unchecked, the package name will automatically be created using the names "com.<database name>.model" and "com.<database name>.dao" etc.

data.name: pbHelpAllowSerialization.ToolTip
data.value: If checked, LayerGen will automatically create methods that allow data to be serialized in various formats, such as JSON and XML. These methods will require a reference to Newtonsoft's Json.Net library, which can be freely downloaded from their website.

data.name: pbHelpDynamicDataRetrieval.ToolTip
data.value: If checked, code will be generated that will allow you to retrieve data through a Sql statement or a stored procedure and dynamically bind it to a strongly typed class. This feature will require .NET 4.0 or higher.

data.name: pbHelpCustomNamespaceNames.ToolTip
data.value: Check this box if you want to create custom namespace names for both the data and business layers. If this box is unchecked, the namespace name will automatically be created using the names "DataLayer.<database name>" and "BusinessLayer.<database name>".
